                            <comment id="490937" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2026 16:39:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Mikhail Pershin &amp;lt;mpershin@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64503&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64503&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19962&quot; title=&quot;don&amp;#39;t use MGC with non-initialized export&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mgc: don&apos;t reference MGC without export&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 602fe0f3a56de92da904e217765f2dd65b09c4dc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="490915" author="tappro" created="Wed, 11 Mar 2026 15:07:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Solution could be just additional check for &lt;tt&gt;cl_mgc_mgsexp&lt;/tt&gt; when decision is made to re-use MGC:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;diff --git a/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c b/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c
index a6cc062631..29162ca395 100644
--- a/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c
+++ b/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c
@@ -355,7 +355,7 @@ int lustre_start_mgc(struct super_block *sb)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; GOTO(out_free, rc = -ENOMEM);
&#160;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; obd = class_name2obd(mgcname);
- &#160; &#160; &#160; if (obd &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !obd-&amp;gt;obd_stopping) {
+ &#160; &#160; &#160; if (obd &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !obd-&amp;gt;obd_stopping &amp;amp;&amp;amp; obd-&amp;gt;u.cli.cl_mgc_mgsexp) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; int recov_bk;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This should close race window when MGC setup was failed but MGC can be referenced while obd_stopping is not yet set&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
